    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced chorizo</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until golden and crispy</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pan-cheesy-chorizo-and-pea-risotto-with-seed-topping/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the chorizo is cooking, peel and finely dice your <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pan-cheesy-chorizo-and-pea-risotto-with-seed-topping/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chorizo is golden and crispy, transfer it to a plate and set aside</p><p>Return the pan to a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pan-cheesy-chorizo-and-pea-risotto-with-seed-topping/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 750ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[975ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.4L] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pan-cheesy-chorizo-and-pea-risotto-with-seed-topping/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add your <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong>, <strong>arborio rice</strong> and the <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and cook for 1 min, stirring to coat the grains in the oil</p><p>Add the <strong>chicken stock</strong> a ladle at a time, stirring continuously for 25-30 min or until all of the stock is absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pan-cheesy-chorizo-and-pea-risotto-with-seed-topping/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Trim, then chop your <strong>green beans </strong>into bite size pieces</p><p>Grate your <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pan-cheesy-chorizo-and-pea-risotto-with-seed-topping/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the rice is cooked, add the <strong>chopped green beans </strong>and cook for 2-3 min</p><p>Add your <strong>blanched peas </strong>and cook for 1 min further or until the green beans are tender and the peas are warmed through</p><p>Stir through a knob of <strong>butter</strong> with most of the <strong>grated cheese</strong> and most of the <strong>crispy</strong> <strong>chorizo</strong> (save some for garnish!) \u2013 this is your<strong> one pan cheesy chorizo & pea risotto</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pan-cheesy-chorizo-and-pea-risotto-with-seed-topping/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>one pan</strong> <strong>cheesy chorizo & pea risotto</strong> topped with the <strong>reserved grated</strong> <strong>cheese</strong>, <strong>reserved crispy chorizo </strong>and a grind of<strong> black pepper</strong></p><p>Garnish with your <strong>3 seed mix</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
